OL,3,CJudgment 'before Easter' in trial of
OL,4,Cdouble sectarian murder accused
OL,6,FMr Murphy concluded by telling Mr
OL,7,FJustice O'Hara the "combined
OL,8,Fcircumstances of this case" and the
OL,9,Flack of any evidence or explanation
OL,10,Fgiven by Smyth "led to an inevitable
OL,11,Fconclusion that Mr Convie and Mr Fox
OL,12,Fwere murdered by Mr Smyth.
OL,14,F"We respectively submit that he should
OL,15,Fbe found guilty on all counts."
OL,17,FNext to address the trial judge was
OL,18,Fdefence barrister Michael Borrelli KC,
OL,19,Fwho said the Crown had failed to prove
OL,20,Fbeyond reasonable doubt that Smyth was
OL,21,Fthe gunman.
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G7/10
