OL,3,CJudgment 'before Easter' in trial of
OL,4,Cdouble sectarian murder accused
OL,6,F"You are dealing with a man who is an
OL,7,Fimpulsive, professional liar and of
OL,8,Fcourse he can give detail about these
OL,9,Foffences because he was involved in
OL,10,Fit."
OL,12,FThe defence barrister also raised the
OL,13,Fissue of eye witness accounts of the
OL,14,Fgunman, all of who spoke of a man
OL,15,F"noticeably taller" than Mr Smyth.
OL,17,FAfter listening to closing
OL,18,Fsubmissions, Mr Justice O'Hara said:
OL,19,F"I will now consider my judgement
OL,20,Fwhich will be given before Easter."
